Shaker Aamer has been held at Guantanamo Bay without charge or trial for 13 years . 
  The 48-year-old is expected to be released in the summer after 13 years in captivity . 
  US government sources say he is likely to be freed as early as June . 
  Mr Aamer is the longest-serving UK resident at the notorious prison camp . 
  He has been cleared for release twice and has a British wife and four children in London . 
 